---
title: `$form::button()`
description: Create a HTML `<button>` element.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Form::button($name = null, $value = null, $text = "", $attr = [], $dent = 0);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$test = Form::button('x', 'on', 'Activate');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = '<button name="x" type="button" value="on">Activate</button>';
~~~